'''Viktor Tobias Johansson''' (born 14 September 1998) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|StokeCty}} club [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] and the  [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

A product of the [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby]] and [[Aston Villa F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Aston Villa]] academies, Johansson spent two years at [[Premier League]] side [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] but only appeared in [[EFL Trophy]] matches for their U21 side. He joined [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] in September 2020. In [[2021–22 Rotherham United F.C. season|2021–22]] he helped Rotherham gain promotion to the Championship and win the [[2022 EFL Trophy final|EFL Trophy]]. He spent four seasons at the [[New York Stadium]] before leaving for [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] in May 2024.

He has represented Sweden at youth and senior international levels.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Johansson spent his early career with Stuvsta, [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby]], [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], [[Alfreton Town F.C.|Alfreton Town]] and [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref name = "SW"/><ref name = "international">{{Cite web|url=https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/landslag/landslagsdatabas/landslagsspelare/?fplid=cd5f525f-e089-4014-9499-7b69edac1c64|title=Landslagsdatabasen: Viktor Johansson|website=svenskfotboll.se|access-date=1 December 2020|archive-date=20 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120212304/https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/landslag/landslagsdatabas/landslagsspelare/?fplid=cd5f525f-e089-4014-9499-7b69edac1c64|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lcfc.com/news/794444|title=Swedish Goalkeeper Viktor Johansson Joins Development Squad|website=lcfc.com|access-date=2 May 2024|archive-date=2 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502111908/https://www.lcfc.com/news/794444|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Rotherham United===
[[File:Viktorjohansson (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|Johansson training with [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] in 2020.]]
In September 2020 he signed for [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]].<ref name="auto">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54000615|title=Rotherham sign goalkeeper Johansson|work=BBC Sport|archive-date=21 January 2021|access-date=2 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121002243/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54000615|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his first appearance in a 2–1 win at home against [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] on 7 November 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themillers.co.uk/news/2020/november/match-report-for-rotherham-united-vs-preston-north-end-on-07-nov-20/|title=REPORT &#124; Rotherham 2 v 1 Preston|website=themillers.co.uk|access-date=8 November 2020|archive-date=7 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107171940/https://www.themillers.co.uk/news/2020/november/match-report-for-rotherham-united-vs-preston-north-end-on-07-nov-20/|url-status=live}}</ref> Johansson was praised for his performances in [[2020–21 Rotherham United F.C. season|2020–21]] and he received the club's Young Player of the Year award.<ref name=ypoty /> The Millers suffered relegation on the final day of the season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Cardiff City 1–1 Rotherham: Paul Warne's Millers relegated to Sky Bet League One |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/cardiff-city-vs-rotherham-united/430249 |website=Sky Sports |access-date=4 July 2024 |archive-date=23 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250223025718/https://www.skysports.com/football/cardiff-city-vs-rotherham-united/430249 |url-status=live }}</ref> Johansson helped Rotherham gain an instant return to the Championship in [[2021–22 Rotherham United F.C. season|2021–22]] finishing 2nd and also winning the [[2022 EFL Trophy final|EFL Trophy final]] at [[Wembley Stadium|Wembley]] after beating [[Sutton United F.C.|Sutton United]] 4–2.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gillingham 0–2 Rotherham: Rarmani Edmonds-Green, Georgie Kelly secure promotion |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/gillingham-vs-rotherham-united/448434 |website=Sky Sports |access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Long|first1=Dan |title=Rotherham 4–2 Sutton AET: Paul Warne's Millers win 2021/22 Papa John's Trophy|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11747/12576898/rotherham-4-2-sutton-aet-paul-warne-s-millers-win-2021-22-papa-john-s-trophy|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]}}</ref>

Johansson later recorded the Championship's highest goals prevented statistic of 8.5 goals prevented across the entire season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4685335/2023/08/02/efl-ones-to-watch-viktor-johansson/|title=EFL ones to watch – Rotherham's Viktor Johansson: From non-League to the Sweden squad|first=Nancy Froston and Thom|last=Harris|website=The Athletic|date=2 August 2023|archive-date=1 April 2025|access-date=13 June 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250401045050/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4685335/2023/08/02/efl-ones-to-watch-viktor-johansson/|url-status=live}}</ref> Johansson was linked with moves away from the club throughout the season<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.leeds-live.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/who-viktor-johansson-rotherham-united-27187890|title=Viktor Johansson enjoys 'outstanding' campaign prompts Leeds United links|first=Matty|last=Hewitt|date=24 June 2023|website=Leeds Live}}</ref> but he opted to sign a new contract with the club, running until summer 2025.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64188230|title=Rotherham keeper Johansson signs new contract|work=BBC Sport|archive-date=2 May 2024|access-date=2 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502180756/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64188230|url-status=live}}</ref> His performances were recognised by the club and manager, winning his first Player of the Year award.<ref name=playeroftheyear>{{cite news |title=The Advertiser's Rotherham United Player of the Year, plus what fans have had to say about him
|url=https://www.rotherhamadvertiser.co.uk/sport/football/rotherham-united/the-advertisers-rotherham-united-player-of-the-year-plus-what-fans-have-had-to-say-about-him-4322935|work=Rotherham Advertiser |date=18 May 2023}}</ref> Manager [[Matt Taylor (footballer, born 1982)|Matt Taylor]] singled out Johansson as the star performer in the team stating ''"he's the best goalkeeper in the championship"'' and his shot stopping ability was at times "in the world class category."<ref>{{Cite news |first=Paul |last=Davis |work=Rotherham Advertiser |date=15 October 2023 |url=https://www.rotherhamadvertiser.co.uk/sport/football/rotherham-united/rotherham-united-player-ratings-marks-for-matt-taylors-men-so-far-this-season-4372702|title=Rotherham United player ratings … marks for Matt Taylor's men so far this season}}</ref>

Following relegation in the [[2023–24 Rotherham United F.C. season|2023–24 season]], local media reported that Johansson had a £1&nbsp;million relegation release clause in his contract.<ref name=beers>{{cite web |last1=Wobschall |first1=Leon |title=Beers are on Rotherham United keeper Viktor Johansson as Sheffield United target reveals incredible fans' gesture ahead of final-day game with Cardiff City |url=https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/beers-are-on-rotherham-united-keeper-viktor-johansson-as-sheffield-united-target-reveals-incredible-fans-gesture-ahead-of-final-day-game-with-cardiff-city-4613508 |work=Yorkshire Post |date=2 May 2024 |access-date=2 May 2024 |archive-date=2 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502111905/https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/beers-are-on-rotherham-united-keeper-viktor-johansson-as-sheffield-united-target-reveals-incredible-fans-gesture-ahead-of-final-day-game-with-cardiff-city-4613508 |url-status=live }}</ref> As a thank you to the Rotherham United fans, Johansson paid for 600 free pints of beer prior to the club's last game of the season against Cardiff City.<ref name=beers />

===Stoke City===
Johansson joined [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] on 18 May 2024, signing a three-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=Goalkeeper Johansson makes Stoke City move |url=https://www.stokecityfc.com/news/2024/may/18/Goalkeeper-Johansson-makes-Stoke-City-move/ |website=Stoke City |date=18 May 2024 |access-date=18 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cjmml0zv722o|title=Stoke sign goalkeeper Viktor Johansson from Rotherham|date=18 May 2024|website=BBC Sport|access-date=19 May 2024|archive-date=19 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240519163028/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cjmml0zv722o|url-status=live}}</ref> Johansson played in all 46 of Stoke's Championship matches in [[2024–25 Stoke City F.C. season|2024–25]],<ref name="2024/25"/> as they avoided relegation on the final day of the season, finishing in 18th.<ref>{{cite web |title=Derby County 0–0 Stoke City: Both teams survive after goalless draw |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/derby-county-vs-stoke-city/509886 |website=Sky Sports |access-date=8 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Staying up a relief, not a celebration – Johansson |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/ce8g5n33yjyo |website=BBC Sport |date=5 May 2025 |access-date=8 May 2025}}</ref> His performances during the season saw him named as [[Stoke City F.C. Player of the Year|player of the year]].<ref name="POTY">{{cite web|title=City's super Swede scoops Player of the Season award|url=https://www.stokecityfc.com/news/2025/april/25/citys-super-swede-scoops-player-of-the-season-award/|website=Stoke City|accessdate=8 May 2024}}</ref> In [[2025–26 Stoke City F.C. season|2025–26]], Johansson, was an ever-present up until he dislocated his shoulder playing against [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] on 29 December 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title='Hit us for six' - Viktor Johansson and Robert Bozenik injury updates as Stoke win at Hull |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/stoke-city-hull-mark-robins-10733114 |website=Stoke Sentinel |access-date=24 May 2026}}</ref> After undergoing surgery he made his first-team return for the season finale against [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Johansson and Tchamadeu return to start season finale |url=https://www.stokecityfc.com/news/2026/may/02/johansson-and-tchamadeu-return-to-start-season-finale/ |website=Stoke City |access-date=24 May 2026}}</ref>

On 1 May 2026, Johansson signed a new four-year deal with Stoke.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stokecityfc.com/news/2026/may/01/citys-super-swede-signs-new-four-year-contract/|title=City's super Swede signs new four-year contract|website=www.stokecityfc.com|date=1 May 2026|accessdate=1 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Johansson has represented Sweden at [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|under-17]], [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21]] youth levels.<ref name = "SW"/><ref name="auto"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/viktor-johansson/cd5f525f-e089-4014-9499-7b69edac1c64/ |title=Viktor Johansson – Spelarstatistik – Svensk fotboll |website=svenskfotboll.se |date=18 November 2019 |access-date=7 November 2020 |archive-date=28 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210728161348/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/viktor-johansson/cd5f525f-e089-4014-9499-7b69edac1c64/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> In March 2023, he received his first call-up to the [[Sweden men's national football team|Swedish senior national team]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] matches against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] and [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 March 2023 |title=Truppen till första EM-kvalmatcherna |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2023/03/trupp-till-forsta-em-kvalmatcherna/ |access-date=19 March 2023 |website=[[Swedish Football Association]] |language=sv |archive-date=16 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230316165554/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2023/03/trupp-till-forsta-em-kvalmatcherna/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Johansson received his first cap for Sweden when he came on at half time against Moldova in October 2023.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Davis |first1=Paul |title=Rotherham United goalkeeper Viktor Johansson wins his first Sweden international cap |url=https://www.rotherhamadvertiser.co.uk/sport/football/rotherham-united/rotherham-united-goalkeeper-viktor-johansson-wins-his-first-sweden-international-cap-4370474 |work=Rotherham Advertiser |date=12 October 2023 |access-date=2 May 2024 |archive-date=12 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231112062953/https://www.rotherhamadvertiser.co.uk/sport/football/rotherham-united/rotherham-united-goalkeeper-viktor-johansson-wins-his-first-sweden-international-cap-4370474 |url-status=live }}</ref>

He was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c3r29z5yz79o|title=Sweden World Cup squad: Alexander Isak and Viktor Gyokeres among those selected|date=12 May 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

